{
  "stem": "9725.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I think it's the first time when we really came face to face what camps were like because as we were given the first food there in sort of battered tin bowls and looked very unappetizing, I saw there were some other girls who had just come back.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And told us that they had come back from the camps in which they work.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were on their way to Auschwitz because they were either maimed or contracted tuberculosis.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember particularly one girl with enormous eyes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She must have been about my age.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She looked at the food, and I asked her if, if she wanted.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I didn't want to eat that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You know it was sand at the bottom and horrible things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Little did I realize what was in store for me and how much that food would have meant later.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I remember I gave her that food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I-- she said she was going-- they were going to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She knew it that in a few days, she would be no more.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That was sort of the first confrontation with, with what there was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Anyway, we, we were sent two days later to-- actually it was like a slave market.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because our names and our ages and the places we hailed from were registered, and industrialists from all over Germany would come to buy slaves.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I mean not literally buy them, but they paid us in 10 German reichsmarks for the processing of, of our papers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And since we came from Bielitz, which was known for textile factories, as fate would have it that particular day a man came from [GERMAN], which was one of the largest textile factories in Germany.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
